              p.lead
                | My name's John, and I'm an undergraduate Junior at the University of California, San Diego studying Computer Science.  I started with an internship my Dad gave me at Four Seasons Chemicals, where I built a business website out of HTML5, CSS3, JS, and PHP.  At the time, I didn't really have the programmatical concepts that I do right now, and that's why I want to write this blog for you all!
                br
                br
                | Nodejs is a beautiful language, now combine that with the awesomeness of MongoDB to easily store non-relational information in a database that fetches data to your desire.  Finally, couple that with responsive design using Bootstrap and open-source front-end resources that are easily tuneable to your every need and you got a web application that's production ready.  Of course it's not that simple, but it all starts with the basics, as I did. I started learning Nodejs in my Sophomore year in college, and even then many of my concepts were flawed.  I had no idea what semaphores were in the context of MongoDB even though I was using it, nor did I have any idea what it meant for Nodejs to be asynchronous, as I wrote callback within callback within callback, that utterly slowed down the program dramatically.
                br
